home.desc: Explore GitHub open source graph data to gain insights into development behaviors and community ecosystems. For example: contributions, partners, interests, community, ecosystem, etc...
home.repository-placeholder: Please enter the GitHub repository name
home.account-placeholder: Please enter the GitHub account name

project.desc1: Discover core project contributors: Identify core contributors based on project development activities (Issues, PRs, Commits, CRs, etc.).
project.desc2: Insight into project ecosystem partners: Extract inter-project development activities, organizations, and other related information to construct the core ecosystem relationships of the project.
project.desc3: Analyze the distribution of the project community: Extract core developers' community distribution based on project development activities and developer organizations.
project.desc4: Showcasing individual open-source contributions: Find core projects participated in based on developer development activities (Issues, PRs, Commits, CRs, etc.).
project.desc5: Finding open-source partners: Find other developers in the open-source community who collaborate closely with you.
project.desc6: Discover individual open-source interests: Analyze the developer's technical domain and interests based on the themes and tags of the projects participated in.
